puzzle.description:
Given a tree and an integer. Find all the nodes that are equal to the integer and give the sum of their direct children. (Leaf count as 0).

f8 :: Tree Int -> Int -> Int
hints: It's similar to the task we learnt: Create list of tuples (node, left child, right child) for odd numbers

testCases.input: print $ f8 (Node 3 (Node 1 Leaf Leaf) (Node 1 Leaf Leaf)) 3
print $ f8 (Node 2 (Node 1 Leaf Leaf) (Node 2 (Node 3 Leaf Leaf) (Node 1 Leaf Leaf))) 2

puzzle.description:
Reverse a tree.
Write a function to create mirror image of a tree.

Example: See task 0 in HW.
hints: How can we construct a new tree using the idea of flipping all left and right subtrees?

testCases.input: reverseTree (Node 1 (Node 2  (Node 4 Leaf Leaf)   (Node 5 Leaf Leaf))  (Node 3 (Node 6 Leaf Leaf)  Leaf))
testCases.expectedOutput: Node 1 (Node 3 Leaf (Node 6 Leaf Leaf)) (Node 2 (Node 5 Leaf Leaf) (Node 4 Leaf Leaf))

testCases.input: reverseTree (Node 5 (Node 10 (Node 31 (Node 1 Leaf Leaf) Leaf) Leaf)  (Node 17 (Node 31 (Node 14 (Node 12 Leaf Leaf) Leaf) Leaf) (Node 11 Leaf Leaf)))
testCases.expectedOutput: Node 5 (Node 17 (Node 11 Leaf Leaf) (Node 31 Leaf (Node 14 Leaf (Node 12 Leaf Leaf)))) (Node 10 Leaf (Node 31 Leaf (Node 1 Leaf Leaf)))

puzzle.description:
Given a value determine in which level it is stored in the given Tree Int.
If the value is not in the tree then return -1

Example: See Task 1 in HW.
hints: Maybe we need to write a helper function that introduces a new parameter to store information about the current level during the recursion.
It's a similar case as task 4. Create list of tuples (node, left child, right child) for odd numbers' nodes. Since we want to get the information about the subtrees of current node.
How do we know if a tree is only one leaf or has at least one node?

puzzle.description:
data Item = Item {
    key :: String,
    value :: Int
} deriving (Show, Eq)

Task a.
    Given a tree of Item. Find the key of the item which has the maximum value.
	All the key inside tree are unique.
hints: How do we campare two items?
Search for the item in the tree or in the list (turn a tree into a list first).
Return the key of the item.

puzzle.description:
data Item = Item {
    key :: String,
    value :: Int
} deriving (Show, Eq)

Task b:  
    Union of two item lists

Union here means taking all the items from both lists, if items has the same key, taking the larger value.

The final result should be distinct in term of key and can be any order!
hints: How do we check if an item is in a list of items?
When we find the item in both lists, we return the item with larger value.

testCases.expectedOutput: [Item {key = "pqr", value = 23},Item {key = "abc", value = 13},Item {key = "def", value = 30},Item {key = "ghi", value = 8},Item {key = "jkl", value = 15},Item {key = "mno", value = 20}]
